gameRecap.title: Game Recap: Timberwolves 129, Bucks 105
gameRecap.excerpt: The Timberwolves defeated the Bucks, 129-105. Anthony Edwards recorded 26 points and nine assists for the Timberwolves, while Karl-Anthony Towns added 19 points (4-6 3PM) and five rebounds in the victory. AJ Green notched a career-high 27 points and seven 3PM for the Bucks in the losing effort. The Timberwolves improve to 36-16 on the season, while the Bucks fall to 33-19.
